An 18-year-old soldier has died after the car he was travelling in crashed into a house.

Josh Powell was travelling in a silver Peugeot 306 convertible with a 25-year-old man in Barnsley, South Yorkshire, at 3.15am this morning.

South Yorkshire Police say the car left the road negotiating a slight left-hand bend, hitting a street lamp and continuing along the footpath, through a garden and into the front of a local property, causing extensive damage to a boundary wall and the front of the house.

