The 25-year-old, who has not been named, is at Barnsley District General Hospital with 'life-threatening injuries', the police have said.

It is not clear which of the two men, both of Grimethorpe, South Yorkshire, were driving, but it is understood they were the only occupants of the car.

Officers believe the car was travelling in excess of the speed limit when it left the road.

The owners of the property the car smashed into, Carl and Julie Jackson, have asked that floral tributes are not left near the address.

