Mrs Jackson, a 49-year-old cleaner, said: 'Our bedroom is right above the living room, which is where the car crashed into. We heard this massive bang, it felt like an earthquake.'

Mr Jackson said: 'I looked out of the window and saw this car on its side upside down outside our house.

'I could see smoke coming from it so I told Julie we needed to get out. Our grandaughter and son were in the house so we got them up and all went outside, I was worried the car was going to burst into flames.

